The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation
		 Sunday, August 15, 2004 				 Film awards
																								New Delhi, Aug. 14: Gautam Ghose has been named best director and screenplay writer for Abar Aranye in the national film awards announced today.																								Sharmila Tagore won the best supporting actress for the same film.																								Rituparno Ghoshs Chokher Bali was adjudged the best film in Bengali. It got the best art director award for Indranil Ghosh and the best costume designers award for B.B. Ray and Shushanto Pal.																								The best cinematography award went to Abhik Mukhopadhyay for Gautam Haldars Bhalo Theko. The film also won the best audiography prize for Anup Mukhopadhyay and Deepon Chatterjee.																								Munnabhai MBBS was named the best film providing wholesome entertainment, while Marathi movie Shwaas was adjudged the best feature film.
